Correct. He said that this is our house,
this is the police station and that's you.

722
01:10:02,717 --> 01:10:03,706
That's me?

723
01:10:03,785 --> 01:10:05,810
Yeah.
He made you Chief of Police, so...

724
01:10:05,887 --> 01:10:07,286
l've gained 20 pounds.

725
01:10:07,355 --> 01:10:10,916
-lt must be the uniform.
-lt's the dangers of a desk job.

726
01:10:11,626 --> 01:10:14,094
l'd like to report a lost purse.

727
01:10:14,829 --> 01:10:16,854
Why don't you have a seat?

728
01:10:25,106 --> 01:10:27,301
-l'm living with this every day.
-What about your marriage?

729
01:10:27,375 --> 01:10:28,740
-What marriage?
-You just don't give up!

730
01:10:28,810 --> 01:10:30,778
-Jack is sleeping in his study!
-He's trying.

731
01:10:30,845 --> 01:10:32,642
You have to find a way to keep going.

732
01:10:32,713 --> 01:10:33,907
-Mother...
-You don't have a choice.

733
01:10:33,981 --> 01:10:37,246
-l am coping with this.
-You can't give up. You have to...

734
01:10:37,318 --> 01:10:38,444
-Oh, no, Mother.
-Bingo!

735
01:10:38,519 --> 01:10:39,679
That is cooking sherry!

736
01:10:39,754 --> 01:10:42,348
-Please! Please!
-You have to find a way to live with this.

737
01:10:42,423 --> 01:10:45,187
-Live with it? l am living with this!
-You're not!

738
01:10:45,259 --> 01:10:47,386
-l'm dealing... l'm coping...
-You don't go into Susie's room.

739
01:10:47,462 --> 01:10:49,862
-l'm dealing with it! So what?
-You won't let anybody touch her things!

740
01:10:49,931 --> 01:10:52,832
You have a tomb
in the middle of your house!

741
01:10:54,802 --> 01:10:57,293
Sweetheart, do you really think
if you seal it up

742
01:10:57,371 --> 01:10:59,771
that the pain's going to go away?

743
01:12:04,338 --> 01:12:07,171
<i>My mother went as far away</i>
<i>as she could.</i>

744
01:12:07,241 --> 01:12:11,439
<i>She found a job in a small orchard</i>
<i>outside of Santa Rosa.</i>

745
01:12:11,512 --> 01:12:14,413
<i>The work was hard, but she didn't mind.</i>

746
01:12:16,250 --> 01:12:19,981
<i>lf anyone asked,</i>
<i>she said she had two children.</i>

747
01:12:36,337 --> 01:12:37,736
<i>And Lindsey,</i>

748
01:12:38,606 --> 01:12:41,404
<i>who always said</i>
<i>she didn't believe in love,</i>

749
01:12:43,044 --> 01:12:44,636
<i>found it anyway.</i>

750
01:13:07,969 --> 01:13:09,493
<i>And there it was.</i>

751
01:13:10,071 --> 01:13:12,301
<i>The moment l would never have.</i>

752
01:13:14,408 --> 01:13:16,876
<i>My little sister had run ahead of me.</i>

753
01:13:18,546 --> 01:13:20,275
<i>She was growing up.</i>

754
01:13:24,819 --> 01:13:27,720
What's the matter?
l thought you'd be happy.

755
01:13:28,623 --> 01:13:29,988
l am happy.

756
01:13:34,161 --> 01:13:35,685
l'm very happy.

757
01:13:36,330 --> 01:13:38,298
Then why are you crying?

758
01:13:39,667 --> 01:13:41,862
No. You think she did not want
to kiss him?

759
01:13:41,936 --> 01:13:42,960
No.

760
01:13:44,372 --> 01:13:45,600
She did.

761
01:13:47,608 --> 01:13:50,008
She wanted to kiss him very much.

762
01:14:03,290 --> 01:14:05,918
<i>Always, l would watch Ray.</i>

763
01:14:07,228 --> 01:14:09,355
<i>l was in the air around him.</i>

764
01:14:10,531 --> 01:14:14,558
<i>l was in the cold winter mornings</i>
<i>he spent with Ruth Connors,</i>

765
01:14:15,703 --> 01:14:18,536
<i>that strange, otherworldly girl</i>

766
01:14:18,606 --> 01:14:23,600
<i>who so easily accepted the presence</i>
<i>of the dead among the living.</i>

767
01:14:29,050 --> 01:14:32,076
<i>And sometimes, Ray would think of me.</i>

768
01:14:34,221 --> 01:14:36,712
<i>But he began to wonder,</i>

769
01:14:36,791 --> 01:14:39,624
<i>maybe it was time</i>
<i>to put that memory away.</i>

770
01:14:41,796 --> 01:14:44,094
<i>Maybe it was time to let me go.</i>

771
01:14:50,905 --> 01:14:52,395
What was that?

772
01:14:52,473 --> 01:14:55,101
-l'm sorry.
-What was... What was that?

773
01:15:04,318 --> 01:15:05,979
Lindsey, throw it!

774
01:15:51,031 --> 01:15:53,966
<i>My murderer had finely tuned instincts.</i>

775
01:15:54,902 --> 01:15:57,166
<i>He knew my sister had begun to wonder</i>

776
01:15:57,238 --> 01:16:00,730
<i>about the solitary man</i>
<i>who lived in the green house.</i>

777
01:16:02,810 --> 01:16:05,244
<i>She seemed intent on crowding him,</i>

778
01:16:06,647 --> 01:16:08,376
<i>and he resented it.</i>

779
01:16:27,334 --> 01:16:31,202
<i>He began to feel a familiar itch.</i>

780
01:17:31,165 --> 01:17:33,224
-Mom, look!
-Just a second.

781
01:17:43,744 --> 01:17:44,870
Careful, honey.

782
01:17:45,946 --> 01:17:47,038
Mom!

783
01:17:54,622 --> 01:17:57,455
<i>Pretty, aren't they?</i>
<i>They are so beautiful.</i>

784
01:19:21,842 --> 01:19:23,173
Mom, look!

785
01:19:24,745 --> 01:19:26,235
Hey, Dad, look at me!

786
01:20:42,589 --> 01:20:44,113
Mr. Salmon.

787
01:20:44,191 --> 01:20:45,215
Hi.

788
01:20:48,962 --> 01:20:50,429
What is that?

789
01:20:52,599 --> 01:20:54,965
lt's just a project l'm working on.

790
01:20:55,035 --> 01:20:57,367
-You're a hunter?
-Ducks.

791
01:21:00,374 --> 01:21:02,501
-That's a blind, right?
-Yep.

792
01:21:03,444 --> 01:21:06,140
-So those things really work?
-Oh, yeah.

793
01:21:08,615 --> 01:21:12,210
lt's all about concealment,
the art of concealment,

794
01:21:13,120 --> 01:21:14,815
and patience.

795
01:21:14,888 --> 01:21:18,790
lt takes a lot of patience.
l sit for hours on end in the dark.

796
01:21:19,693 --> 01:21:21,320
l'm an outdoorsman.

797
01:21:21,829 --> 01:21:23,456
Always have been.

798
01:21:46,653 --> 01:21:48,018
Mr. Salmon?

799
01:21:51,992 --> 01:21:53,789
l just...

800
01:21:53,861 --> 01:21:57,820
l never got a chance to tell you
how sorry l am about your loss.

801
01:22:23,690 --> 01:22:24,918
<i>Dad.</i>

802
01:22:45,646 --> 01:22:48,513
Here. Let me. Let me help you.

803
01:22:48,582 --> 01:22:50,277
Oh, no. That's all right.
Really, l can manage.

804
01:22:50,350 --> 01:22:52,113
No, it's no trouble.

805
01:22:55,022 --> 01:22:56,353
All right.

806
01:22:56,990 --> 01:22:58,480
Appreciate it.

807
01:23:03,497 --> 01:23:04,794
This is for you.

808
01:23:04,865 --> 01:23:07,732
Oh, thank you, Mr. Harvey,
you really shouldn't.

809
01:23:08,669 --> 01:23:10,000
-You're welcome.
-Oh, that does smell...

810
01:23:10,070 --> 01:23:11,332
lt's a beautiful smell, isn't it?

811
01:23:13,373 --> 01:23:16,069
-Hey, look at me!
-Careful, honey.

812
01:23:24,017 --> 01:23:27,919
Oh, that really does smell delicious.

813
01:23:28,755 --> 01:23:30,620
-Beautiful, yeah.
-Dad!

814
01:23:30,691 --> 01:23:33,353
They are something.

815
01:23:33,860 --> 01:23:35,657
Hey, Dad, look at me!

816
01:24:02,456 --> 01:24:05,823
l think it's time for you to go home now,
Mr. Salmon.

817
01:24:17,170 --> 01:24:18,535
Go on home.

818
01:24:25,746 --> 01:24:27,077
l'm sorry.

819
01:24:28,682 --> 01:24:30,309
l can't help you.

820
01:24:32,019 --> 01:24:35,819
What did you do to her?
What did you do to my daughter?

821
01:24:35,889 --> 01:24:37,789
Tell me! Where is she?

822
01:24:39,026 --> 01:24:40,493
lt's got to stop, Jack!

823
01:24:40,560 --> 01:24:42,926
You came this close
to getting arrested tonight!

824
01:24:42,996 --> 01:24:45,624
You're lucky George Harvey declined
to press charges.

825
01:24:45,699 --> 01:24:47,257
Lucky?

826
01:24:47,334 --> 01:24:49,461
Your father put a hole
in the man's back door.

827
01:24:49,536 --> 01:24:51,265
Yeah, he should have put a hole
in his head.

828
01:24:51,338 --> 01:24:53,306
-Lindsey, please.
-Did you hear that, Jack?

829
01:24:53,373 --> 01:24:55,273
This is the example you're setting
for your kids?

830
01:24:55,342 --> 01:24:56,434
Persecuting the neighbors!

831
01:24:56,510 --> 01:24:58,341
-He's not crazy!
-l didn't say that.

832
01:24:58,412 --> 01:25:02,371
-Well, then why won't you listen to him?
-Because you need evidence, Lindsey.

833
01:25:02,449 --> 01:25:05,885
You can't go around making
accusations against George Harvey

834
01:25:05,952 --> 01:25:08,887
when you have no evidence.
You need proof.

835
01:25:08,955 --> 01:25:11,048
You are pathetic.

836
01:25:11,124 --> 01:25:12,614
Why can't you just admit it?

837
01:25:12,693 --> 01:25:15,355
You stopped looking for her
a long time ago.

838
01:25:15,429 --> 01:25:16,828
Len's right.

839
01:25:17,864 --> 01:25:19,729
