What's wrong?

965
01:55:16,394 --> 01:55:17,486
Ruth?

966
01:55:40,252 --> 01:55:41,412
Susie?

967
01:55:45,590 --> 01:55:47,922
You wrote me a poem once.

968
01:55:51,263 --> 01:55:53,458
You called yourself the Moor.

969
01:56:03,108 --> 01:56:06,168
That's good. l got it. l'll take it from here.

970
01:56:19,724 --> 01:56:21,248
Kiss me.

971
01:57:27,525 --> 01:57:30,016
You are beautiful, Susie Salmon.

972
01:57:51,716 --> 01:57:56,653
<i>These were the lovely bones</i>
<i>that had grown around my absence.</i>

973
01:57:58,390 --> 01:58:01,917
<i>The connections, sometimes tenuous,</i>

974
01:58:03,728 --> 01:58:06,026
<i>sometimes made at great cost,</i>

975
01:58:07,365 --> 01:58:09,765
<i>but often magnificent</i>

976
01:58:12,170 --> 01:58:14,866
<i>that happened after l was gone.</i>

977
01:58:17,642 --> 01:58:20,042
<i>And l began to see things in a way</i>

978
01:58:21,012 --> 01:58:23,037
<i>that let me hold the world</i>

979
01:58:24,783 --> 01:58:26,410
<i>without me in it.</i>

980
01:58:44,969 --> 01:58:46,937
lt's a cold one tonight!

981
01:58:54,112 --> 01:58:56,012
You looking for a ride?

982
01:58:58,049 --> 01:58:59,107
No.

983
01:59:00,452 --> 01:59:01,476
No?

984
01:59:03,655 --> 01:59:06,146
Are you sure? Pretty cold out here.

985
01:59:08,960 --> 01:59:11,588
l'll take you wherever you want to go.

986
01:59:13,631 --> 01:59:14,996
What do you think?

987
01:59:15,066 --> 01:59:18,467
Look, mister, l'm not interested, okay?

988
01:59:19,571 --> 01:59:23,063
l'm not trying to do nothing.
Just trying to be polite.

989
01:59:23,141 --> 01:59:24,506
That's all.

990
01:59:25,543 --> 01:59:29,411
-A young lady alone at night, not safe.
-Didn't you hear me?

991
01:59:29,481 --> 01:59:30,743
Piss off!

992
02:00:29,207 --> 02:00:32,040
<i>When my mother came to my room,</i>

993
02:00:32,110 --> 02:00:36,740
<i>l realized that all this time</i>
<i>l had been waiting for her.</i>

994
02:00:38,950 --> 02:00:41,077
<i>l had been waiting so long.</i>

995
02:00:42,654 --> 02:00:44,952
<i>l was afraid she wouldn't come.</i>

996
02:00:48,726 --> 02:00:50,387
l love you, Susie.

997
02:01:02,073 --> 02:01:04,701
<i>Nobody notices when we leave.</i>

998
02:01:04,776 --> 02:01:08,371
<i>l mean, the moment</i>
<i>when we really choose to go.</i>

999
02:01:09,647 --> 02:01:14,641
<i>At best, you might feel a whisper</i>
<i>or the wave of a whisper</i>

1000
02:01:15,253 --> 02:01:16,845
<i>undulating down.</i>

1001
02:01:19,591 --> 02:01:22,651
<i>My name is Salmon, like the fish.</i>

1002
02:01:23,828 --> 02:01:25,489
<i>First name, Susie.</i>

1003
02:01:26,764 --> 02:01:29,790
<i>l was 1 4 years old</i>
<i>when l was murdered</i>

1004
02:01:29,868 --> 02:01:33,133
<i>on December 6, 1973.</i>

1005
02:01:37,675 --> 02:01:39,575
<i>l was here for a moment,</i>

1006
02:01:41,813 --> 02:01:43,576
<i>and then l was gone.</i>

1007
02:01:46,284 --> 02:01:49,845
<i>l wish you all a long and happy life.</i>

